args: I just heard some very interesting news\nabout Vixel from a traveling peddler.
Ya mean that conductor we met a while\nback in the snowy town?
The very same. Apparently he's become\nquite the household name.
Guy MUST be a big deal if folks're talkin'\nabout him all the way out here.
It makes me proud to hear about\nacquaintances doing well.
Pardon me, you two, but we have a guest.
I don't remember having any visitations\nscheduled for today.
He has come without an appointment.\nLet me show him in...
We were just talkin' about ya! Sounds like\nyer really rollin' in clover lately, yeah?
Vixel is a most wondrous conductor!
We are but humble performers from an\norchestra, good sir.
Vixel brought us to this castle in order\nto save us.
We come here today to beg a boon of you,\n{player_name}.
It's a request for aid for this orchestra.
You're apparently the biggest conductor\ngoing right now. What can you possibly\nneed from me?
Yes! Vixel is a wondrous conductor!
As you know, a conductor must have an\norchestra—and this one is currently mine.
And while they certainly have skill,\nthey've also one rather grave issue.

And look, if that was the only problem,
we'd be okay. We have instruments,
so we could perform for money and
eventually get square.
But alas, the roof just collapsed at the old\nchurch we use for practice.
This was going to be SUCH a great chance,\ntoo. Imagine, working with THE Vixel!
Anyway, just when we were about to give\nup, Vixel brought us here.
So you're looking for a sponsor, then?\nFinancially, I mean.

With Vixel at our side, our next show is
certain to pack the house—and I assure
you that our talent is second to none!
Your donation will NOT be in vain.
And when IS your next performance?
A date has not yet been decided. However,\nI can vouch for this orchestra's skill.
The concert is certain to be a success.
Well, I suppose it can't hurt to give you\nsome money so you can—
We're in the middle of a war, if you\nhaven't forgotten—and it's not as if\nwe're flush with surplus cash.
We should see a demonstration of skill\nbefore we simply throw coins at these\npeoples' feet like common mummers.
That's a good point. Harsh, but good.
Okay, guys. How about you perform a\nsong for us right here?
If we like what we hear, we'll give you the\nmoney you seek.
Eeek! It's an audition! I... Um...

Hey! Just a second ago you were struttin'
around like ya owned the joint! What
happened to ＂our talent is second to
none＂ and all that malarkey?!
W-well, it's just that we haven't had a\nchance to practice recently, what with\nthe collapsed roof and all.
Enough of this—your skills are true.\nFollow my lead, and all will be well.
Now believe in my baton and entrust\nyourself to the music.
O-okay, Vixel. We'll do our best!
Then let us begin! On three. Ready?
Ya got that right. It sounded pretty, \nbut also packed a hell of a wallop.
This is the first time we've ever played\nthat song so beautifully!
I...can't stop my hands from shaking.\nWas that really US performing?!
What have you done to us, Vixel?
I simply conducted in a manner that\ndrew out such a performance.
You believed in my conducting,\nand thus played the piece majestically.
Thank you for entrusting such a wonderful\nsound to me.
Well, after hearing that, I'm ready to\noffer you all whatever you need.
What other choice is there after\nthat performance?
Then our audition was a success.\nThank you, {player_name}.
No, thank YOU. That was amazing.
I'll be looking forward to the day I can\nhear you all perform on a grand stage.
That was but the prelude, after all.\nNo more than an overture.
